# Add Authorization Policy ‚Äî Procedure

Authorization is **backend-only**. Policies live in `common/policies/`; guards in `common/guards/`. Matrix: `docs/07_SECURITY_IMPLEMENTATION.md` B√∂l√ºm 5.3; patterns ‚Üí `12-backend-authorization.mdc`.

## Step 0: Preconditions

- [ ] Access rule defined in `docs/01_DOMAIN_MODEL.md` visibility section.
- [ ] `docs/07_SECURITY_IMPLEMENTATION.md` matrix row exists or will be added.
- [ ] Understand 404 vs 403 semantics ([AUTH-004]).

Load: `docs/07_SECURITY_IMPLEMENTATION.md` B√∂l√ºm 5, `docs/04_BACKEND_SPEC.md` B√∂l√ºm 5, `docs/01_DOMAIN_MODEL.md` (visibility).

## Step 1: Identify Resource and Actions

| Resource | Policy file | Typical actions |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Campaign | `campaign.policy.ts` | read, update, delete, invite |
| Character | `character.policy.ts` | read, write, live-update |
| Homebrew | `homebrew.policy.ts` | read, update, publish |
| Collection | `collection.policy.ts` | read, add, remove |
| DM Note | `dm-note.policy.ts` | read, write (DM only) |

Actions align with `packages/shared` `Action` / `Resource` enums when using central `can()` dispatcher.

## Step 2: Implement Policy Function

```typescript
// apps/api/src/common/policies/campaign.policy.ts
export class CampaignPolicy {
  static canRead(user: AuthUser, campaign: CampaignWithMembers): boolean {
    if (user?.role === Role.ADMIN) return true; // always first ‚Äî [AUTH-008]
    if (!user) return false;
    if (campaign.ownerId === user.id) return true;
    return campaign.members.some((m) => m.userId === user.id);
  }

  static canUpdate(user: AuthUser, campaign: Campaign): boolean {
    if (user?.role === Role.ADMIN) return true;
    if (!user) return false;
    return campaign.ownerId === user.id;
  }
}
```

Rules:

- **ADMIN bypass** first line in every check.
- **No caching** ‚Äî runtime DB lookup per request ([AUTH-002]).
- DM/Player are **not** system roles ‚Äî derive from `ownerId` / `campaign_members`.
- Deactivated user content hidden from normal users; ADMIN sees ([AP-002]).

## Step 3: Wire in Service (Not Controller)

```typescript
const campaign = await this.prisma.campaign.findUnique({
  where: { id },
  include: { members: true },
});

if (!campaign || !CampaignPolicy.canRead(user, campaign)) {
  throw new NotFoundException();
}

if (!CampaignPolicy.canUpdate(user, campaign)) {
  throw new ForbiddenException({
    error: 'FORBIDDEN',
    message: 'You do not have permission to update this campaign',
  });
}
```

| Situation | HTTP | Rationale |
| --- | --- | --- |
| No resource or no read access | **404** | Hide existence |
| Resource visible, write denied | **403** | User knows resource exists |
| Email not verified on write | **403** | `EMAIL_NOT_VERIFIED` |
| No/invalid token | **401** | JwtAuthGuard |

Campaign is **fully private** ‚Äî non-members get 404 on detail, empty list on collection.

## Step 4: Guards and Decorators

Global guards (`APP_GUARD`):

| Guard | Trigger |
| --- | --- |
| `JwtAuthGuard` | default; skip with `@Public()` |
| `EmailVerifiedGuard` | `@RequireVerifiedEmail()` |
| `RolesGuard` | `@Roles(Role.ADMIN)` |

Do not duplicate `@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard)` unless overriding global stack.

WebSocket room join ‚Üí membership check in gateway (`docs/07` B√∂l√ºm 6, `@47-websocket-live-fields`).

