## Anti-patterns

- ‚ùå Inline `if (ownerId !== user.id)` in controller
- ‚ùå 403 for stranger reading private campaign (leaks existence)
- ‚ùå Cached membership for authorization
- ‚ùå Frontend-only access control
- ‚ùå Policy change without integration tests in same PR

## Resource-Specific Notes

### Campaign

List endpoint returns only campaigns where user is DM or member. Stranger never sees other's campaign in list.

### Character

`PUBLIC` visibility ‚Üí guest read OK. `PRIVATE` without campaign ‚Üí owner + ADMIN only. Assigned to campaign ‚Üí all campaign members read; write: owner or DM.

### Homebrew

`DRAFT` ‚Üí owner (+ ADMIN). `PUBLISHED` ‚Üí gallery public read. Publish transition may need `canPublish` check.

### DM Notes

DM only (`campaign.ownerId`). Players ‚Üí 404 on all dm-notes routes.

### Admin

`@Roles(Role.ADMIN)` on controller; policy bypass still documented in service for clarity.

## Email Visibility [SEC / PII]

`email` in API response only when `requester.id === user.id` or ADMIN. Policy does not expose email in list endpoints for other users.

## Deactivated Users [AP-002]

Content from `is_active = false` users hidden from normal users in gallery/lists; ADMIN sees. Add test cases when touching homebrew/reference visibility.

## WebSocket Authorization

Room join uses same membership rule as campaign read ‚Äî implement in gateway, not separate policy file unless shared helper extracted (`@47-websocket-live-fields`).

